      "role": "user",
      "content": "sometimes i just sit here staring at the ceiling and thinking about how none of this actually matters. like cosmically. the sun is gonna burn out, the universe is heading for heat death, and every single thing we do, every person we love, every struggle we have... it's just noise that gets deleted anyway. it feels so stupid to even try to keep going when the math says it all ends in zero.",
